WEBVTT

00:04.766 --> 00:05.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.766 --> 00:07.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.166 --> 00:09.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
On the "NewsHour"
tonight: in the hot seat.

00:09.333 --> 00:14.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
FBI Director James Comey
defends his decision to
reopen an investigation
into Hillary Clinton's

00:15.766 --> 00:19.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
e-mails, days before last
year's presidential election.

00:19.900 --> 00:22.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Then, bridging the
health care divide.

00:22.700 --> 00:27.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Republicans try to win over
no votes in their own ranks by
putting more money on the table

00:28.833 --> 00:31.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to cover those with
preexisting conditions.

00:31.666 --> 00:36.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And in our final report from
South Sudan, how violence
against women is being used as

00:37.300 --> 00:39.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
a weapon of war.

00:39.300 --> 00:43.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WINNIE BYANYIMA, Oxfam
International: They told
me that: We long for peace.

00:43.066 --> 00:47.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
We want to be able to
walk freely and farm
and feed our families.

00:47.566 --> 00:50.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But the solution lies in
resolving the conflict.

00:50.433 --> 00:55.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

00:57.433 --> 00:59.833 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:59.833 --> 01:04.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A tense time
today for the man who runs the
Federal Bureau of Investigation.

01:11.600 --> 01:16.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
James Comey spent hours before
the Senate Judiciary Committee
rejecting criticism that

01:16.566 --> 01:21.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he has mishandled
investigations of Hillary
Clinton or Donald Trump.

01:21.433 --> 01:23.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Lisa Desjardins has the story.

01:23.566 --> 01:26.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAMES COMEY, FBI Director: I
have lived my entire career
by the tradition of that, if

01:26.833 --> 01:31.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
you can possibly avoid it, you
avoid any action in the run-up
to an election that might have

01:31.233 --> 01:34.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
an impact, whether it's
a dogcatcher election or
president of the United States.

01:34.466 --> 01:38.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But, today,
FBI Director James Comey
faced the charges that he did

01:38.900 --> 01:43.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
impact the 2016 presidential
election, when he sent this
letter to Congress on October

01:45.933 --> 01:49.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
28, 11 days before Election
Day, revealing new steps in
an investigation into Hillary

01:50.533 --> 01:51.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Clinton's e-mail practices.

01:51.533 --> 01:53.733 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

01:53.733 --> 01:56.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DIANNE FEINSTEIN (D),
California: I have one
question, and I view
it as a most important

01:56.400 --> 01:59.000 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
question.

01:59.000 --> 02:01.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Ranking
Democrat Dianne Feinstein
asked today why he broke
normal FBI protocol.

02:01.233 --> 02:05.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JAMES COMEY: I could
see two doors, and
they were both actions.

02:05.833 --> 02:08.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
One was labeled speak, and
the other was labeled conceal.

02:08.500 --> 02:10.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Look, this was terrible.

02:10.600 --> 02:14.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It makes me mildly nauseous
to think that we have had
some impact on the election.

02:14.233 --> 02:17.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But, honestly, it wouldn't
change the decision.

02:17.600 --> 02:21.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Everybody who disagrees with
me has to come back to October
28 with me, and stare at this

02:21.766 --> 02:23.166 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and tell me what you would do.

02:23.166 --> 02:24.400 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

02:24.400 --> 02:26.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
DIANNE FEINSTEIN: You
took an enormous gamble.

02:26.900 --> 02:30.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The gamble was that there
was something there that
would invalidate her
candidacy, and there

02:34.266 --> 02:36.266 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
wasn't.

02:36.266 --> 02:38.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Democrats
also pointed out that Comey had
been silent at the time about

02:38.900 --> 02:42.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the ongoing investigation into
Trump campaign ties to Russia.

02:42.866 --> 02:47.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He argued there was a
difference, that he had
previously told Congress
the Clinton probe

02:47.366 --> 02:50.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
was closed and he
needed to reverse that.

02:50.666 --> 02:54.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he insisted to Hawaii
Democrat Mazie Hirono
that he was impartial:

02:54.666 --> 02:58.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAMES COMEY: I wasn't thinking
of what effect it might have
on a political campaign.

02:58.633 --> 03:00.766 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:00.766 --> 03:03.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAZIE HIRONO (D), Hawaii: I
find that hard to believe that
you didn't contemplate that

03:03.466 --> 03:07.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
there would be political
ramifications to your comments.

03:07.533 --> 03:09.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I'm just wondering why...

03:09.033 --> 03:10.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JAMES COMEY: I knew there
would be ramifications.

03:10.233 --> 03:12.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I just tried not
to care about them.

03:12.266 --> 03:15.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: Texas
Republican John Cornyn
defended Comey and
pointed back at Clinton.

03:15.933 --> 03:18.000 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:18.000 --> 03:20.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN CORNYN (R), Texas: You
are not the one who made the
decision to handle classified

03:20.533 --> 03:22.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
information on a
private e-mail server.

03:22.533 --> 03:25.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The hearing
was full of other news as well.

03:25.766 --> 03:28.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Lindsey Graham of South Carolina
pressed Comey on Russia.

03:28.066 --> 03:30.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:30.100 --> 03:31.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LINDSEY GRAHAM (R), South
Carolina: Is it fair to say
that the Russian government is

03:31.366 --> 03:33.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
still involved in
American politics?

03:33.433 --> 03:37.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JAMES COMEY: Yes, well,
certainly, in my view,
the greatest threat of
any nation on Earth,

03:39.166 --> 03:41.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
given their intention
and their capability.

03:41.200 --> 03:46.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: And on
issues of privacy, Comey said
encryption has blocked the FBI

03:46.100 --> 03:49.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
from getting data off devices
in nearly half its cases.

03:49.533 --> 03:51.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JAMES COMEY: None of
us want backdoors.

03:51.733 --> 03:55.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We don't want access to
devices built in, in some way.

03:55.733 --> 03:59.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What we want to work with
manufacturers on is to figure
out, how can we accommodate both

03:59.933 --> 04:01.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
interests in a sensible way?

04:01.533 --> 04:03.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS:
One more hot topic?

04:03.533 --> 04:06.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Trump's proposed
ban on immigrants from
some Muslim countries.

04:06.766 --> 04:08.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Vermont Democrat Patrick Leahy:

04:08.000 --> 04:09.466 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

04:09.466 --> 04:10.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PATRICK LEAHY (D), Vermont: Does
that make America less safe?

04:10.466 --> 04:12.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JAMES COMEY: Senator, thank you.

04:12.533 --> 04:16.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm not going to comment on
the particular statement, but
I do agree that a perception

04:16.400 --> 04:21.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
or reality of hostility towards
any community, but in this --
particularly the Muslim American

04:22.333 --> 04:24.300 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
community, makes
our jobs harder.

04:24.300 --> 04:28.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: As for his
own job, Comey's 10-year
term runs out in 2023.

04:28.033 --> 04:32.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm Lisa
Desjardins at the U.S. Capitol.

04:32.266 --> 04:36.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In the day's
other news: The U.S. House of
Representatives easily approved

04:36.433 --> 04:39.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a compromise bill to fund the
government through September.

04:39.900 --> 04:41.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That's the end of
this fiscal year.

04:41.866 --> 04:46.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It totals $1.1 trillion, and
it includes an increase in
defense spending, but it ignores

04:48.666 --> 04:52.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
several other of President
Trump's priorities, including
money for a border wall.

04:55.266 --> 04:58.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Leaders on both sides
praised the rare example
of cooperation between
Republicans and Democrats.

04:58.766 --> 05:00.733 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

05:00.733 --> 05:02.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL RYAN (R-WI), Speaker
of the House: This is a
bipartisan piece of legislation.

05:02.800 --> 05:07.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so each side doesn't get
everything they want, but we
are able to come together and

05:08.600 --> 05:10.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
find a package that advances
many of our important goals.

05:10.666 --> 05:13.200 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

05:13.200 --> 05:15.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STENY HOYER (D-MD),
Minority Whip: Democratic
members' participation
is absolutely essential

05:15.200 --> 05:19.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
if we're going to pass fiscal
bills and appropriation bills.

05:19.066 --> 05:23.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I'm glad that the Republican
leadership and negotiators
came to that conclusion and

05:23.000 --> 05:26.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
worked with us to advance
this omnibus to the floor.

05:26.166 --> 05:31.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The legislation
now heads to the Senate for
approval before this week is

05:31.100 --> 05:33.666 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
out.

05:33.666 --> 05:37.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A revised Republican plan
to repeal and replace
Obamacare gained key
endorsements in the House

05:37.633 --> 05:39.666 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
today.

05:39.666 --> 05:43.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Moderate Republican Fred Upton
and conservative Billy Long
said they will support the bill.

05:45.633 --> 05:48.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
They spoke after meeting
with President Trump
on their amendment to
help cover people with

05:48.300 --> 05:49.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
preexisting conditions.

05:49.800 --> 05:51.866 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

05:51.866 --> 05:55.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED UPTON (R), Michigan: He
said that this bill would be
just as strong on preexisting

05:55.200 --> 05:58.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
illnesses as Obamacare.

05:58.366 --> 06:01.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I want him to keep that pledge.

06:01.600 --> 06:06.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This amendment allows that to
happen, and cover those that
otherwise might have been

06:07.966 --> 06:09.900 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
excluded.

06:09.900 --> 06:13.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The amendment
adds $8 billion to the
bill over five years.

06:15.900 --> 06:18.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Leaders of the House
conservative Freedom
Caucus endorsed the
proposal, and said that

06:18.500 --> 06:21.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the vast majority of their
members will support it.

06:21.833 --> 06:25.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But as of the time we
went on the air, no
vote has been scheduled.

06:25.966 --> 06:30.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In Eastern Missouri, another
wave of heavy rain is adding
to a flood emergency that's

06:30.933 --> 06:33.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
already claimed five lives.

06:33.000 --> 06:38.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The swollen Meramec River neared
an all-time high in suburban
Saint Louis today, damaging

06:39.300 --> 06:43.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
200 homes and threatening
some 1,500 more.

06:43.300 --> 06:48.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Parts of two interstate highways
are also underwater, and a
section of the Mississippi

06:48.133 --> 06:50.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
River is closed.

06:50.200 --> 06:54.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The U.S. Justice Department
confirmed today it will not
charge two white policemen in

06:56.366 --> 06:59.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the killing of a black man
in Baton Rouge, Louisiana.

06:59.533 --> 07:04.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Cell phone video from last
July showed Alton Sterling
pinned, but struggling.

07:06.500 --> 07:09.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One officer yelled that
he was reaching for a
gun, and then he shot him.

07:09.200 --> 07:14.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In Baton Rouge today, U.S.
attorney Corey Amundson said
there are no solid grounds for

07:15.066 --> 07:17.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
a civil rights violation.

07:17.100 --> 07:20.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
COREY AMUNDSON, Acting U.S.
Attorney: After an exhaustive,
almost year-long investigation,

07:22.566 --> 07:27.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
all of the prosecutors and
agents involved in this case
have come to the conclusion that

07:29.600 --> 07:34.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
insufficient evidence exists
to charge either officer with
a federal crime in connection

07:35.233 --> 07:37.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with this incident.

07:37.266 --> 07:41.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The attorney
general of Louisiana says that
he will now investigate whether

07:41.233 --> 07:45.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
state criminal charges should
be filed against the officers.

07:45.333 --> 07:50.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
North Korea confirmed
today that it has detained
another American citizen.

07:50.066 --> 07:55.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
State TV said that Kim Sang
Dok, an instructor at Pyongyang
University, was picked up on

07:55.966 --> 07:57.466 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
last month.

07:57.466 --> 07:59.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He is accused of acts aimed at
overthrowing the government.

07:59.900 --> 08:04.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
