and I'm going to try to keep

12:59.433 --> 13:02.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
my question as
basic as possible.

13:02.166 --> 13:06.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Congressman, I'm sure you know
the American Medical Association
has come out today saying

13:06.433 --> 13:08.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
they are still opposed.

13:08.500 --> 13:12.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They are worried that millions
of people are going to be left
out with preexisting conditions.

13:12.166 --> 13:17.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The AARP, retired
persons association, says
they're still opposed.

13:19.100 --> 13:22.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the American Cancer Society
says they have taken a look
at this, and they say every

13:22.033 --> 13:27.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
bit of history for anything
that looks anything like this
high-risk pool arrangement that

13:29.033 --> 13:33.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Congressman Upton has included
