for preexisting conditions
and essential health benefits.

19:54.433 --> 19:58.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I mean, what good is an
insurance policy if you
buy it and you can't
go to the emergency

19:58.666 --> 20:00.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
room and be covered?

20:00.700 --> 20:05.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, yes, Democrats, we're
willing to work on the high
cost of pharmaceuticals.

20:05.333 --> 20:10.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I would really like to get to
the heart of the matter of how
we encourage greater competition

20:10.000 --> 20:13.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in areas of the country that
do not have competition.

20:13.133 --> 20:18.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are a lot of great ideas,
and, hopefully, this will --
this new repeal effort will fail

20:20.133 --> 20:24.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
tomorrow, and we can get down to
brass tacks, to improving what
works and fixing what doesn't.

20:24.166 --> 20:28.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But you're
prepared with the idea that it
may pass, that the Republicans

20:28.466 --> 20:31.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
may now have enough votes
among themselves to get
this through the House?

20:31.766 --> 20:33.200 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

20:33.200 --> 20:35.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
KATHY CASTOR: Boy, they're
